PEP8 - Python Enhancement Proposal

It is used to improve the readability and consistency of the python code. It is a document that consists of how the
naming conventions, code layouts, indentation, comments and whitespaces are to be used while writing a python code.

Flake8

Flake8 is a Python library that is used to check the code base against the coding style PEP8, programming errors
and the cyclomatic complexity

Pylint

Pylint is a source-code, bug and quality checker for the Python code. It follows the style recommended by PEP 8.
It is similar to Pychecker and Pyflakes, but includes the features as below :

1. Checking the length of each line
2. Checking that variable names are well-formed according to the project's coding standard
3. Checking that declared interfaces are truly implemented.

